    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/861: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 26, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. For Reuben Clark.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“7. First. We defer to your judgment regarding realization loan.</p>
                    <p>Second. Aside from special circumstances indicated our 6, our suggestion
                        therein was based on consideration of security back of this loan and fact
                        that it was recently issued to meet critical conditions in Brazilian coffee
                        and exchange situation. These factors led us to conclusion expressed in our
                        6, paragraph first.</p>
                    <p>Third. We fully appreciate difficulties you have had to face in working out
                        adjustment outlined in your No. 4 and we assume from your cable that
                        suggestion of further changes at this time would be futile and possibly
                        harmful to results already achieved. Ex[ecutive] Com[mittee].”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
